{{Orphan|date=April 2014}}


'''Rohit Gadia''' is an [[Indian]] Visionary Entrepreneur. He is the Chief Executive Officer of CapitalVia<ref>{{cite web|title=About CapitalVia|url=http://www.capitalvia.com/about-us.html}}</ref> , Financial Market Research and Consulting Company.

== Personal ==

He did his Schooling at Nehru Montessori Higher Secondary School in [[Burhanpur]]. Rohit graduated from [[Sri Bhagawan Mahaveer Jain College]], [[Bangalore University]] with a degree in [[Commerce]]  and holds master<U+2019>s degree in [[Finance]] from [[S P Jain School of Global Management]], [[Dubai]] / [[Singapore]]. He also holds diplomas in [[Information Technology]] from [[C-DAC]].

== Career ==

He began his career by selling [[SIM Card]] under umbrella and worked with [[Hewlett Packard]] [[BPO]] for a very short duration. In 2006, he started CapitalVia, an investment advisory company which came into operations in June 2008.<ref>{{cite web|title=How Rohit Gadia turned his passion into Rs 13 crore stock trading enterprise|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2012-04-02/news/31275264_1_trading-technical-analysis-pocket-money|publisher=The Economic Times|accessdate=02 April 2012}}</ref>
== Awards ==

In 2010, he was presented S P Jain Alumni Achievement Awards for Professional Excellence<ref>{{cite web|title=S P Jain hosts Alumni Achievement Awards for Professional Excellence|url=http://www.spjain.org/events_spjain_host_alumni_awards.aspx|publisher=S P Jain School of Global Management}}</ref> . He was also named as winner of ET Now IndiaMART Leaders of Tomorrow Awards 2012 in the Category Banking, Finance and Allied Services<ref>{{cite news|title=Honouring the Growth Enablers|url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Client.asp?skin=pastissues2&enter=LowLevel|accessdate=26 December 2012|newspaper=The Economic Times}}</ref>{{verification failed}}. He was featured on Yahoo <U+2018>True Rags to riches<U+2019> as he figured among the India<U+2019>s most innovative minds which is a talent hunt campaign 'Innovation Jockeys-2' organized by [[Accenture]] across engineering Schools.<ref>{{cite web|title=How a 27 year old created a 13 crore business|url=https://in.specials.yahoo.com/news/how-a-27-year-old-created-a-13-crore-business-110316959.html|publisher=Yahoo|accessdate=27 May 2013}}</ref>
